snippet.title: Amber Heard asked if she'd 'altered images of injuries' ahead of James Corden
snippet.description: Amber Heard was questioned about the build-up to her appearance on James Corden's The Late Late Show in 2015 at the High Court today in London. ¬†The Magic Mike actress, 34, was giving evidence in former spouse Johnny Depp's libel case against News Group Newspapers. ¬†Depp, 57, is suing the publishers over an April 2018 article, written by executive Dan Wootton, in which the Pirates of the Caribbean actor was branded a "wife beater". ¬†Natasha Wass QC, representing Depp, said to Heard it had been suggested the actress had altered images of her injuries ahead of her appearance on James Corden‚Äôs The Late Late Show.  Read More Related Articles  Read More Related Articles  ¬†Heard simply responded: "No." ¬†Lawyer then asked Heard if she had asked anyone else to do it. ¬†Once again, Heard replied: "No." ¬†Heard was then questioned over whether she had used make-up to enhance her injuries in the photographs. ¬†Heard answered: "Only to try and hide them." ¬†Heard was then questioned over images, which were obtained by MailOnline in April 2019 of Depp and Heard‚Äôs broken bed frame that the actress claims Depp broke during a physical altercation, a few days before Christmas in 2015.  ¬†Lawyer asked: "Did you break the bed?" ¬†Heard replied: "No I didn't." ¬†Lawyer then said: "Did you pull out your own hair so you could leave it on the floor to take photographs?" ¬†Heard responded: "No I did not." ¬†Heard was then questioned if she asked anyone else to pull out her hair for the benefit of the photographs. ¬†Heard answered: "No I did not."  ¬†Lawyer then asked why Heard called the nurse a couple of days after the alleged attack. ¬†Heard said she called the nurse "to drop off meds". ¬†Lawyer then asked if the nurse had undertaken a "clinical examination" of her. ¬†Heard responded: "No. She was dropping off meds and she said she was late." ¬†Depp has denied all of Heard's allegations of domestic abuse.
